    <system:String x:Key="Memory.Instruction.1">1. The memory mechanism extracts summaries and key facts from your interactive dialogues as memory vectors.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Memory.Instruction.2">2. Changes to the memory sharing scope affect the isolation level of historical memory loaded by the agent in new sessions.</system:String>

    <system:String x:Key="ContextArrangement.Page.Title">Context Arrangement</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ContextArrangement.Page.Description">Configure context arrangement strategies to optimize large language model tool calls and prompt structures.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ContextArrangement.Page.Hint">Changes will be written to ContextArrangement.xml immediately.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ContextArrangement.OptimizeToolCallPrompt.Label">Optimize tool call prompts</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ContextArrangement.OptimizeToolCallPrompt.Hint">When enabled, the system will optimize tool call descriptions and prompt structures sent to LLMs to improve tool invocation accuracy.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ContextArrangement.ToolCallIdTable.Label">Tool Call ID table</system:String>
